  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shahrukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has received numerous international awards and recognitions throughout his career. Here are some of the notable international awards he has won:\n\n1. **Padma Shri (2005)**\n   - India's fourth-highest civilian award, presented by the Government of India.\n\n2. **Ordre des Arts et des Lettres (2007)**\n   - France's highest civilian award in the field of arts, awarded by the French government.\n\n3. **Legion of Honour (2014)**\n   - France's highest civilian award, presented by the French Ambassador to India.\n\n4. **Special Award at the 20th Annual Crystal Awards (2018)**\n   - Presented by the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, for his contributions to the arts and his humanitarian work.\n\n5. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Edinburgh (2015)**\n   - Awarded for his outstanding contribution to the world of cinema and his charitable work.\n\n6. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Bedfordshire (2009)**\n   - Recognized for his contributions to the Indian film industry and his social work.\n\n7. **Special Honour at the Locarno Film Festival (2013)**\n   - Received the \"Premio Ascona\" for his contribution to cinema.\n\nThese awards reflect Shahrukh Khan's significant impact not only in the Indian film industry but also on the global stage.",
